      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's not just about breathing though. \"taking a step back\" doesn't fix the debt or the fact that i've basically become a laughing stock in my industry. every time i close my eyes i just see their faces, the people i let down. it's like this massive, suffocating pressure in my chest. i feel like i've already died, just my body is still moving around. i don't see how things \"get better\" when the damage is this permanent. everything i built is just ash now.",
